dc_description_s: These data layers represent zoning for Outagamie County, Wisconsin in 2018. It is a feature class within the geodatabase Outagamie_Zoning_2018.gdb. The feature layers included in this geodatabase are NOutagamie_Airport_2018N, NOutagamie_General_2018N, and NOutagamie_Shoreland_2018N.Airport: [This feature class was derived off of the 1990 Zoning Ordinance Z-16-90. This ordinance covers airport property, the airport industrial park and the airport overylay districts. Zone 3A was created in March of 2012.]General: [This is a polygon geodatabase depicting the local zoning of parcels under Outagamie County Zoning jurisdiction. Outagamie County created new zoning maps for the areas of the County that have exclusive agriculture zoning that are under County jurisdiction. The County also updated the text of the County Zoning Ordinance to meet requirements enforced by DATCP to meet requirements of chapter 91 of the Wisconsin State Statutes dealing with farmland preservation starting in 2013.]Shoreland: [This is a polygon dataset identifying the location of all navigable water buffers within Outagamie County. It is a county-wide file including all USGS designated navigable waterways.]
dct_provenance_s: Arthur H. Robinson Map Library - University of Wisconsin
dc_subject_sm: Zoning - Maps, City Planning, County Ordinances
